cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CY

This paper deals with the resilience of classification algorithms to attacks on training data, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cybersecurity (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cyber-physical systems (cs.SY), and control theory (cs.CY). However, since the paper focuses on the use of data-driven techniques in cyber-physical systems, and specifically on the resilience of linear classification algorithms, it is most likely to belong to cs.LG and cs.CR, followed by cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.CY.
